`cde.desktop`:
Adds the CDE session entry to display managers (`/usr/share/wayland-sessions`).

`cde-session`:
Session launcher that starts optional desktop services (`picom`, `dunst`) and runs CDE in Wayland mode with `/etc/cde/default_config.py`.

`cde`:
Convenience launcher (`cde start`, `cde session`, `cde settings`) used by the desktop entry and terminal usage.

`default_config.py`:
System-wide CDE window-manager config. Floating-only workflow with taskbar and launcher keybinds.

`cde-settings`:
Small GUI app to update CDE user settings at `~/.config/cde/settings.json`.

`cde-settings.desktop`:
Desktop launcher entry for the CDE Settings app.

`99-cde.rules`:
udev rules used by CDE-supported hardware integrations.
